JOHANNESBURG – The foreign ministers of the Brics emerging economies have criticised what they call a “new wave of protectionism,” in reference to US President Donald Trump’s tough trade negotiations with key economic partners. READ: Sisulu says SA is committed to multilateral diplomacy The envoys from Brazil, Russia, India, China and South Africa, which was represented by International Relations minister Lindiwe Sisulu, referred to “unilateral measures that are incompatible with” international trade rules after a meeting Monday in the South African administrative capital of Pretoria, AP reported. China on Sunday warned the US that results of trade talks would be void if Washington went ahead with imposing tariffs on Chinese goods, as negotiations came to an end in Beijing. - Additional reporting by AFP African News Agency